    "ja": null,
    "latex": "**Erdős Problem 42**: Let M ≥ 1 and N be sufficiently large in terms of M. Is it true that for every\nmaximal Sidon set `A ⊆ {1,…,N}` there is another Sidon set `B ⊆ {1,…,N}` of size M such that\n`(A - A) ∩ (B - B) = {0}`?",
